<h3>Austin Stories</h3>

<p>Austin Stories first debuted in 1999 simply as a list of web writers in Central Texas who keep online journals.</p>

<p>As a community of these writers began to develop, the list was relaunched as a &quot;portal&quot;, by which readers can follow their favorite writers. A journal writer wishing to post to the portal must first register for an account. (The writer must also demonstrate some familiarity with the Central Texas area.)</p>

<p>Once approved, members may then post to the site whenever they update their own journals or weblogs. Austin Stories also supports Movable Type's Trackback system, allowing members to send pings instead.</p>

<p>Austin Stories does require a degree of editorial judgment, so even though it accepts pings, members must still make sure their posts conform to publishing guidelines.</p>

<p>If members provide URLs of their RSS feeds, Austin Stories can parse and aggregate them, allowing readers even more ways to keep up-to-date.</p>
